The paper discusses efficient implementation of linear programming decoding for low-density parity-check (LDPC) codes. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT), as LDPC codes are commonly used in communication systems. The paper also involves optimization techniques (cs.DS) and linear programming (cs.DC), which are relevant sub-categories. The proposed preconditioning algorithm is similar to the encoding procedure of LDPC codes, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses computer simulation results, which is a common aspect of machine learning (cs.LG).
